// NPM understanding
// NPM - Node Package Manager
// NPM is a package manager for Node.js, allowing developers to share and reuse code.


// Insatalling and uninstalling anything basics & advance
//install -> npm install <package_name>
//uninstall -> npm uninstall <package_name>
//install with specific version -> npm install <package_name>@<version>


// understanding node modules
// node_modules - directory where all installed packages are stored

//dependencies
//packages and packages ki dependencies

// devdependencies
//aise packages jo sirf development mai kaam aayege par jab app ban jaayega aur uplod ho jaayega tab hum in packages ko use nhi kar rahe honge.
// Example: npm i nodemon --save-dev


// script - understanding default scripts PATH and custom scripts
//default scripts - npm start, npm test, npm run build
//custom scripts - npm run <script_name>
